This paper deals with natural language processing and graph modeling, which are both relevant to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of Max-Margin Markov Graph Models (M3GM) and Exponential Random Graph Model (ERGM) also suggests that this paper could be relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of graph-theoretic properties of the entire net could also be relevant to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
